\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2054727 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs22\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\fs18\insrsid2054727\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Abstract}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs18\insrsid2054727\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
The number of anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) injuries in athletes is estimated to be around 200,000 per year in the United States, with a disproportionate impact on collegiate populations because of the high-intensity cutting and pivoting activities of 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
competitive sport. This paper presents a machine learning pipeline to measure the Cutting Signature, a combination of three designed biomechanical proxy features (Fatigue Accumulation, Lateral Force Proxy, Symmetry Index), and a systematic six-way techniq
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ue\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 tournament to identify the best combination of class-imbalance treatment and probability calibration to deploy the system to clinical use. Three heterogeneous datasets of 6,430 athlete-seasons are integrated to a canonical 15-feature schema, which result
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 s in 10.6% injury prevalence (1:8.4 ratio). All six modular configurations swap precisely one block of the previous: SMOTE (T0, control)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  -> }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ADASYN (T1) -> BorderlineSMOTE (T2) -> Cost-Sensitive Learning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 (T3) -> Platt calibration (T4) -> }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
sotonic calibration (T5, proposed). Monotonic results on a 20% stratified hold-out indicate improvement in all measures: T5 attains AUC = 0.831, Recall = 0.846, F1 = 0.808, and Brier Score = 0.0741, a 25.6% improvement over the SMOTE control (BS = 0.0996)
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  and 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 1.8% below the no-skill prevalence predictor.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs18 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs18\cf23\insrsid3883073\charrsid883800 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 The isotonic-calibrated model meets the Clinical Trust property: a reported 65% risk score is associated with a 65% ACL injury rate in that score range that is empirically validated. Post-hoc SHAP analysis validates engineered Cutting Signature features 
