\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi360\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9658332 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid2054727\charrsid2054727 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Even though the reviewed literature contributes greatly to the field, it fails to cover three gaps that are interrelated. To begin with, no existing production-scale pipeline combines several heterogeneous cohorts (different sports, institutions, and data
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  collection modalities) on to one canonical schema}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid9658332 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid2054727\charrsid2054727 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 most research uses a single cohort of a single institute. Second, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid9658332 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 prior}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs20\insrsid2054727\charrsid2054727 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 research on ML-based ACL prediction has not created a multi-gender and multi-sport model that was trained on more than one dataset at a time, which limits the possibility to determine cross-population generalizability. Third, existing approaches are eith
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 er prohibitively expensive to 3D MoCap }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid9658332\charrsid2054727 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 instrument or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs20\insrsid2054727\charrsid2054727 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  restricted to small wearable-sensor pilots (N < 50); a large-scale pipeline, with training-load variables and with N tested to sc\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
ale to N > 6,000), is not found in the literature.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s19\qj \li0\ri148\sb2\sl237\slmult1\nowidctlpar\tx508\wrapdefault\nocwrap\nooverflow\faauto\rin148\lin0\itap0\pararsid2054727 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
