The present work directly addresses all three gaps: it fuses three distinct Kaggle-sourced datasets }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid5982586 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
spanning male and female collegiate athletes across multiple sport contexts into a 6,430-row master dataset; it engineers biomechanical proxies computable from training-load data without specialized instrumentation; and it demonstrates that a Stackable En
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 semble trained on this unified dataset achieves Mean AUC-ROC = 0.81, exceeding the Random Forest benchmark of Guo \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 [3] and substantially exceeding the 3D Mo-Cap based SVM of Jauhiainen 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 [1], while remaining deployable in resource-constrained collegiate athletic training environments.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid2054727 
