\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 The current findings have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\cf23\insrsid4863857 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 several }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\cf23\insrsid4863857\charrsid4863857 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
limitations. To begin with, the three source datasets are observational, measured through self-reported or GPS-estimated training load as opposed to validated 3D motion capture, the Cutting Signature proxy features are approximations, not biomechanical me
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
asurements. Second, the isotonic calibrator is configured with cv=3 on the 80% training partition; a bigger calibration holdout or leave-one-out cross-validation would decrease variance in the calibration function estimate at the expense of training data.
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  T\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
hird, the current model fails to reflect the temporal dynamics: the risk of injury accumulation is over days and weeks, not reflected in instantaneous feature values. The natural extension of the architecture is incorporation of recurrent architectures (L
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
STM or temporal convolutional networks) over rolling 7-day load windows. Lastly, it must be validated externally on an independent cohort with ground-truth ACL injury outcomes before clinical implementation. The probability calibration presented here is a
